#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:4
#: 6deaa3f55a7f475b8b90205313ba3f71
msgid "What is beneficial ownership?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:6
#: 2390aeba9af04a848d7be31a5eee1cee
msgid "The concept of beneficial ownership helps us understand how companies and other legal entities are owned and controlled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:13
#: 50cd38ab11ff47658c87d86fb905940d
msgid "Companies or people can own other companies..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:19
#: 38854bc92c0243fe805643a6e65ddc60
msgid "The idea that people own companies and sometimes companies own companies is well understood."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:None
#: 60335e43439542ad842132e2b0e51e5f
msgid "Person A owns 100% of Company 1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:29
#: 1bdb4e4232284c729b3f17a6e88d7cfb
msgid "...but it's people that ultimately benefit..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:35
#: 040c5bce50bf4405a6b6f4d10b5c41d6
msgid "Even when companies own companies, individuals almost always appear at the end of the ownership chain. They ultimately benefit from companies’ financial successes, and often share in their failures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:None
#: f68815503c2f45f587147e26e214bb4e
msgid "Company 2 owns 100% of Company 3's shares. And Person B owns\n"
"30% of Company 2's shares"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:43
#: cc23946598bf4f6390b838e35829369c
msgid "Here, Company 2 acts as an intermediary in a chain of ownership."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:49
#: 5f4563f2f6b248e387a16adbe81f3480
msgid "...so, we need to know who ultimately controls a company..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:55
#: 5ea1b05195184162a94d2dd3472c6d96
msgid "If a person owns something, they usually have some control over it. Owning shares in a company may confer voting rights, for example. But ownership and control are sometimes separated - by share classes, contracts, agreements and other mechanisms. For example, an executive director might have the right to appoint 60% of the other board members, while having little financial stake in the business."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:None
#: b09cb4e5363d4411ae8bb228bd98cd1c
msgid "Person B owns 30% of Company 2's shares. And Person C (an\n"
"executive director) has the right to appoint 60% of Company 2's board\n"
"members"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:67
#: 18b2eb6c84334a21badd0f9257ed551d
msgid "Significant control over a company’s composition and decisions may be used to steer benefits and direct risks. Those people taking the financial risks for a company may not be the ones making the decisions. In which case, we need to know who is in control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:76
#: 39980db758bb4560a9db66d8a61e0ada
msgid "...to see the big picture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:82
#: 59ac35cbffc34012b173644b076ed5e8
msgid "Beneficial ownership therefore takes in both types of involvement with a company: ownership and control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../primer/whatisbo.rst:87
#: 9e269c77d46a4be0ae3dee1bed234e0a
msgid "**Beneficial ownership** is the right to some share of a legal entity's income or assets (ownership) or the right to direct or influence the entity's activities (control)."
msgstr ""
